last_episode_to_air.name: Come Along With Me
last_episode_to_air.overview: In the distant future, many years after the outcome of the Gum War, two friends named Beth and Shermy recover a rusty old mechanical arm that once belonged to Finn after it is dropped by a Prize Ball Guardian.

tvs.name: Adventure Time
tvs.overview: Hook up with Finn and Jake as they travel the Land of Ooo searching for adventure. But remember, adventure isn’t always easy. Sometimes you’ve got to battle fire gnomes that torture old ladies, save a smelly hot dog princess from the Ice King, and thaw out a bunch of frozen businessmen. What the cabbage?!

episodes.name: Adventure Time (Pilot)
episodes.overview: Princess Bubblegum is imprisoned by the Ice King. Jake and Finn battle their way past the Iceclops, Snow Golem, and other monsters that inhabit the Ice Kingdom to rescue her.

episodes.name: The Wand
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake come across a magic wand, but when the wand becomes uncontrollable, they must team up with the Ice King to stop it.

episodes.name: How an Idea Becomes Adventure Time
episodes.overview: Pen Ward, Adam Muto and Kent Osborne discuss their experiences working on Adventure Time.

episodes.name: All's Well That Rats Swell
episodes.overview: BMO discovers a rogue rat in the tree house's flour and attempts to drive off the creature.

episodes.name: Have You Seen the Muffin Mess
episodes.overview: Jake and Finn assist Princess Bubblegum in attempting to stop a muffin-based plague.

episodes.name: Sow, do you like them Apples
episodes.overview: Ice King and Marceline are hungry for a snack.

episodes.name: The Gift that Reaps Giving
episodes.overview: Death tries to make a mixtape for his girlfriend, Life.

episodes.name: Good Jubies: The Making of Bad Jubies
episodes.overview: A behind-the-scenes look at the making of Season 7, Episode 20 "Bad Jubies".

episodes.name: Frog Seasons: Spring
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake are compelled to follow a frog carrying a crown.

episodes.name: Frog Seasons: Summer
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake are in for a surprise when they force the hand of fate.

episodes.name: Frog Seasons: Autumn
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake discover the power held by the crown.

episodes.name: Frog Seasons: Winter
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake follow the frog into the Ice Kingdom. Will they finally bear witness to the purpose of the crown?

episodes.name: Frog Seasons: Spring (Again)
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake come full circle in their pursuit of frog royalty.

episodes.name: Diamonds and Lemons
episodes.overview: Finn and his friends experience setbacks and creative triumphs in a fantastic new vision of Ooo.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: Soon after airing, the show began to receive critical acclaim as well as a large fan following. In 2010, the Adventure Time episode "My Two Favorite People" was even nominated for a Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Short-format Animated Program, although the series did not win.

guest_stars.character: Mr. Cream Puff / Mr. Cupcake / Chet (voice)
guest_stars.name: Dee Bradley Baker

guest_stars.character: Zombie Candy Heart / Peppermint Butler / Gumball Guardian #2 (voice)
guest_stars.name: Steve Little

episodes.name: Slumber Party Panic
episodes.overview: Finn and Princess Bubblegum must protect the Candy Kingdom from a horde of candy zombies they accidentally created.

episodes.name: Trouble in Lumpy Space
episodes.overview: Finn must travel to Lumpy Space to find a cure that will save Jake, who was accidentally bitten by Lumpy Space Princess at a tea party.

episodes.name: Prisoners of Love
episodes.overview: When the Ice King kidnaps a number of princesses he sees as potential brides, Finn and Jake team with the prisoners to set everybody free.

episodes.name: Tree Trunks
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake join Tree Trunks in search for the rare Crystal Gem Apple, but question whether Tree Trunks has what it takes to adventure.

episodes.name: The Enchiridion!
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake go on a quest for a magical book that would prove them worthy of being righteous heroes.

episodes.name: The Jiggler
episodes.overview: A jiggly creature attracted by Finn's auto-tuned singing follows Finn and Jake home but soon feels ill effects of separation from its family.

episodes.name: Ricardio the Heart Guy
episodes.overview: When a Heart Guy named Ricardio comes to Candy Kingdom, Finn gets really jealous and finds a way to get him out of the Land of Ooo.

episodes.name: Business Time
episodes.overview: When Finn and Jake discover a group of businessmen frozen in an iceberg, the duo thaws them and hires them to help with their adventures.

episodes.name: My Two Favorite People
episodes.overview: Jake's plan to spend time with both Lady Rainicorn and Finn backfires.

episodes.name: Memories of Boom Boom Mountain
episodes.overview: Finn reflects on an upsetting experience in his past and pledges to help everyone in town, but this proves more difficult than imagined.

episodes.name: Wizard
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake temporarily get magic powers from an evil wizard, but are tricked into helping stop a comet.

episodes.name: Evicted!
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake search the land of Ooo for a new home after Marceline claims the duo's treehouse as her own.

episodes.name: City of Thieves
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake go off to face a thief king who has been stealing from little girls.

episodes.name: The Witch's Garden
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake consider breaking up after a witch strips Jake of his powers.

episodes.name: What Is Life?
episodes.overview: Finn brings a pie-throwing robot to life, but the machine begins to long for a more fulfilling existence.

episodes.name: Ocean of Fear
episodes.overview: Finn struggles to overcome his fear of the ocean.

episodes.name: When Wedding Bells Thaw
episodes.overview: The Ice King gets married but not before he convinces Finn and Jake to throw him a manlorette party.

episodes.name: Dungeon
episodes.overview: Finn's headstrong decision to explore a dungeon in defiance of Jake's warnings leads to a dangerous escapade.

episodes.name: The Duke
episodes.overview: Finn must tell the truth when he accidentally turns Princess Bubblegum bald and green and blames the Duke of Nuts.

episodes.name: Freak City
episodes.overview: After being transformed into a foot, Finn joins forces with a band of misfits to make things right.

episodes.name: Donny
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake try to help an obnoxious grass ogre named Donny develop better social skills, only to find out Donny's jerky behavior protects the house people from the why-wolves, which eat the house people.

episodes.name: Henchman
episodes.overview: After seeing Marceline the vampire queen torment an elderly henchman, Finn steps in to be her new henchman, doing whatever he is told to do.

episodes.name: Rainy Day Daydream
episodes.overview: Stuck inside the treehouse due to a knife storm, Finn and Jake use their imagination to pass the time.

episodes.name: What Have You Done?
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake capture the Ice King as their prisoner, but feel guilty when unable to explain the wrongs he committed.

episodes.name: His Hero
episodes.overview: The great warrior Billy inspires Finn and Jake to practice nonviolence, but the duo finds it difficult to resist old ways.

episodes.name: The Gut Grinder
episodes.overview: When the Fluffy People's gold has been devoured by a culprit only known as "The Gut Grinder", Finn and Jake team up to find him with his tracks.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: In 2011, Adventure Time was nominated for an Annie Award, and the episode "It Came from the Nightosphere" was nominated for a Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Short-format Animated Program.

episodes.name: It Came from the Nightosphere
episodes.overview: Marceline's evil father goes on a soul-sucking rampage after Finn and Marceline accidentally release him from the Nightosphere.

episodes.name: The Eyes
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake try to rid themselves of a weird horse that creeps them out.

episodes.name: Loyalty to the King
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake are excited to meet the Nice King who has come to Ooo. They soon realize that he looks suspiciously like someone else they know; the Ice King.

episodes.name: Blood Under the Skin
episodes.overview: When Finn gets a splinter on his finger, he wants to get the best armor. In order to receive it, he must go on a quest to get the Magical Armor of Zelderon and survive one embarrassing situation after another.

episodes.name: Story Tellin'
episodes.overview: Jake is sick and demands to hear a good story full of romance, fighting and suspense.

episodes.name: Slow Love
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake agree to help a snail named Snorlock find a girlfriend.

episodes.name: Power Animal
episodes.overview: Finn is captured by gnomes who want to use his energy to power their infernal machines, and it's up to Jake to stay focused and rescue him.

episodes.name: Crystals Have Power
episodes.overview: Jake takes a pledge of nonviolence just before Finn is kidnapped by outlaws from the crystalline dimension.

episodes.name: The Other Tarts
episodes.overview: Finn choses to cross the Desert of Doom to deliver the royal tarts to the annual back rubbing ceremony.

episodes.name: To Cut a Woman's Hair
episodes.overview: A tree witch demands a lock of princess hair else Jake will be sucked into her bottomless bottom.

episodes.name: The Chamber of Frozen Blades
episodes.overview: Whilst the Ice King goes out to take Gunther to the hospital, Finn and Jake decide to sneak inside his lair and flex their ninja skills.

episodes.name: Her Parents
episodes.overview: Jake's relationship with Lady Rainicorn is in danger when he promises to meet with her parents, as both species had a long history of war with each other. However, thanks to Jake's shape-shifting powers, they mistake the dog as one of their own, but for how long?

episodes.name: The Pods
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake discover a box containing three beans. Planting them causes three pods to grow. Two of them are good and one is evil, but which is which?

episodes.name: The Silent King
episodes.overview: After defeating a evil king of goblins, Finn finds himself crowned as their new king. Unfortunately, he's unable to do anything for them due to the rules of the previous king including defending the goblins from the previous king.

episodes.name: The Real You
episodes.overview: Finn has to give a speech at Princess Bubblegum's science barbecue and seeks a quick fix to make himself smarter.

episodes.name: Guardians of Sunshine
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake get sucked into one of BMO's games and they have to defeat all three of his bosses.

episodes.name: Death in Bloom
episodes.overview: After killing Princess Bubblegum's plant when left to take care of it, Finn and Jake make a trip to the Land of the Dead in order to get it's soul back.

episodes.name: Susan Strong
episodes.overview: Finn is excited to discover what appears to be a tribe of humans living underground near the Candy Kingdom, but gets more than he expected when he tries to teach one of them about the surface world.

episodes.name: Mystery Train
episodes.overview: Wanting to surprise Finn on his birthday, Jake takes Finn on a train, where they get wrapped up in a murder mystery.

episodes.name: Go with Me
episodes.overview: Marceline and Jake give Finn advice so he can ask Princess Bubblegum to see a movie with him.

episodes.name: Belly of the Beast
episodes.overview: In order to cure the stomach ache of a giant, Finn and Jake must break up a party happening in his belly.

episodes.name: The Limit
episodes.overview: On a mission to save soldiers of the Hot Dog Princess, Finn and Jake go inside a massive maze where wishes can be granted and where Jake's stretching powers are pushed to their limits.

episodes.name: Video Makers
episodes.overview: After discovering government warnings prior to movies for their film club, Finn and Jake decide to make their own, but get into a fight over the direction of their film.

episodes.name: Mortal Folly
episodes.overview: When the Lich is accidentally freed from its amber prison in Princess Bubblegum's Castle, Finn and Jake must head forth to stop it from regaining its full power, all while being pestered by the Ice King to give him their blessing to marry Princess Bubblegum.

episodes.name: Mortal Recoil
episodes.overview: Princess Bubblegum recovers from being dropped in the Well of Power by the Ice King; however, she is altered and her condition leads to an unlikely final showdown with one of the greatest evils in order to save all life in Ooo.

episodes.name: Heat Signature
episodes.overview: Marceline plays a prank on Finn and Jake by making them believe they're vampires, but it goes too far and escalates when they're manipulated by her ghost friends.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: The season was met with largely positive critical reception. In addition, several episodes and writers were nominated for awards; the episode "Thank You" was nominated for an Annie Award as well as an award at the Sundance Film Festival. "Too Young" was nominated for an Emmy Award. Storyboard artist Rebecca Sugar was also nominated for an Annie Award.

episodes.name: Conquest of Cuteness
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake must defend their home from the Cuties, a tiny race who believe themselves to be evil, destructive invaders.

episodes.name: Morituri te Salutamus
episodes.overview: The duo choose to partake in gladiatorial combat against the Fight King's ghost warriors, but Finn succumbs to bloodlust while Jake becomes obsessed in keeping a cool morale.

episodes.name: Memory of a Memory
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake enter Marceline's mind to awaken her from a sleep spell she had cast on herself, without knowing that they are being tricked by a person from her past.

episodes.name: Hitman
episodes.overview: The grounded Ice King hires a fire-manipulating hitman to attack Finn and Jake, without realizing the potentially deadly consequences.

episodes.name: Too Young
episodes.overview: The Earl of Lemongrab takes over the Candy Kingdom due to Princess Bubblegum's age regression, forcing her and Finn to try and get rid of him even if it means a life-altering decision.

episodes.name: The Monster
episodes.overview: The king and queen of Lumpy Space ask Finn and Jake to bring their daughter back home. At the same time, they attempt to stop a "monster" from destroying a village.

episodes.name: Still
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake are literally unable to move and are at the mercy of the Ice King.

episodes.name: Wizard Battle
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake enter a competition for wizards in disguise so they can prevent Ice King from winning the grand prize: a kiss from Princess Bubblegum.

episodes.name: Fionna and Cake
episodes.overview: In this gender-swapped episode, Fionna and Cake must battle the evil Ice Queen.

episodes.name: What Was Missing
episodes.overview: Finn and his friends must come together as a genuine band in order to open the gate of the Door Lord and get back their taken items.

episodes.name: Apple Thief
episodes.overview: When Tree Trunks's apples go missing, she, Finn and Jake descend into the dark side of the Candy Kingdom in order to find the thief.

episodes.name: The Creeps
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake receive an invitation to a masquerade dinner. It turns into a whodunit as guests start to meet their demise.

episodes.name: From Bad to Worse
episodes.overview: When another plague of Candy Zombies arises and Princess Bubblegum is among the undead, Finn and his friends are in a race against time to figure out how to stop it...without making things even worse!

episodes.name: Beautopia
episodes.overview: Susan Strong asks Finn and Jake to help fight off the Glub Glubs in the sewers below to regain her people's home in Beautopia.

episodes.name: No One Can Hear You
episodes.overview: Finn awakens after an accident to find the Candy Kingdom citizens mysteriously gone and Jake acting crazier than usual.

episodes.name: Jake vs. Me-Mow
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake take on a request to protect Wildberry Princess from an unknown assassin. The assassin turns out to be a tiny cat assassin called Me-Mow, who ends up bribing Jake by poisoning him.

episodes.name: Thank You
episodes.overview: The Snow Golem visits the Fire Kingdom and finds an unlikely follower.

episodes.name: The New Frontier
episodes.overview: Jake dreams about his death, and Finn takes action when events from the dream start to come true.

episodes.name: Holly Jolly Secrets Part I
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake find the Ice King's video diary and have a chance to unearth his secrets.

episodes.name: Holly Jolly Secrets Part II
episodes.overview: The Ice King summons an army of snowmen to recover the secret tapes Finn and Jake are watching. They must work against the clock to find out the secrets enclosed within.

episodes.name: Marceline's Closet
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake play Cloud Hunt in Marceline's house, but they get trapped in her closet after she comes home.

episodes.name: Paper Pete
episodes.overview: Library books seek help from Finn and Jake to save them from the evil Moldari.

episodes.name: Another Way
episodes.overview: Cyclops tears may heal Finn and Jake's broken toes.

episodes.name: Ghost Princess
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake play detective and try to solve Ghost Princess' murder.

episodes.name: Dad's Dungeon
episodes.overview: Jake's dad presents a strange challenge to the guys when he appears to them in a holographic message, telling them about a dungeon he made for them.

episodes.name: Incendium
episodes.overview: Jake embarks on a solo mission to help a broken-hearted Finn.

seasons.name: Season 4
seasons.overview: The season was met with largely positive critical reception. In addition, several episodes were nominated for awards; The episodes "Princess Cookie", "The Hard Easy", "Lady & Peebles", and "Goliad" were all nominated for Annie Awards. The episode "Card Wars", however, won a Golden Reel Awards.

episodes.name: Hot to the Touch
episodes.overview: Finn develops a crush on Flame Princess and tries to get to know her, which proves difficult due to her destructive power.

episodes.name: Five Short Graybles
episodes.overview: Follow as 5 stories intertwine together, can you find the connection?

episodes.name: Web Weirdos
episodes.overview: When Finn gets trapped in a giant spider web, he ends up playing marriage counselor to a couple of grumpy arachnids.

episodes.name: Dream of Love
episodes.overview: Tree Trunks is courted by an oinking suitor, but much to Jake’s dismay, this interferes with her baking habits.

episodes.name: Return to the Nightosphere
episodes.overview: Marceline’s dad banishes Finn and Jake to the Nightosphere, and it stinks. Literally.

episodes.name: Daddy's Little Monster
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake attempt to rescue Marceline and find out what's making her behave so strangely.

episodes.name: In Your Footsteps
episodes.overview: A bear cozies up to the guys, but his true intentions may be hidden.

episodes.name: Hug Wolf
episodes.overview: Finn goes through a transformation after a run-in with a hug wolf.

episodes.name: Princess Monster Wife
episodes.overview: Princesses lose body parts under mysterious circumstances.

episodes.name: Goliad
episodes.overview: Battling with her new realization of her own mortality, in a sleep deprived state Princess bubblegum creates her own heir to the throne. After meeting the heir, Finn and Jake decide to teach her the ways of the world.

episodes.name: Beyond This Earthly Realm
episodes.overview: When Finn finds a porcelain lamb, it transports him into the spirit world and only the Ice King can help get him out.

episodes.name: Gotcha!
episodes.overview: In order to do research for her tell-all memoir about men, Lumpy Space Princess goes undercover working for Finn and Jake.

episodes.name: Princess Cookie
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake are called to solve a Candy Kingdom hostage crisis when a rogue cookie takes over.

episodes.name: Card Wars
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake play Card Quest, an epic game.

episodes.name: Sons of Mars
episodes.overview:
Magic man has most of his power taken from him by his brother, in a fit of desperation, he swaps the way Jake and Himself look.

Magic Mans brother takes Jake to Mars for punishment,

episodes.name: Burning Low
episodes.overview: Princess Bubblegum may be jealous when Finn start hanging out with Flame Princess.

episodes.name: B-Mo Noire
episodes.overview: BMO tries to find Finn's sock.

episodes.name: King Worm
episodes.overview: Finn has a vivid dream that may be more than it seems.

episodes.name: Lady & Peebles
episodes.overview: Princess Bubblegum and Lady Rainicorn look for Finn and Jake, who are missing after a run-in with the Ice King.

episodes.name: You Made Me!
episodes.overview: When a creepy sleep-peeping Lemongrab upsets Princess Bubblegum with his creepy ways, Finn and Jake need to tend to some issues in the Outer Realm.

episodes.name: Who Would Win?
episodes.overview: The guys challenge a monster to a fight but end up battling each other.

episodes.name: Ignition Point
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake sneak into the Fire Kingdom to retrieve Fire Princess' scented candles and overhear a plot to assassinate the king.

episodes.name: The Hard Easy
episodes.overview: Frog People seek protection from an evil lizard who's attacking their swamp.

episodes.name: Reign of Gunters
episodes.overview: The Gunters cause chaos in Ooo

episodes.name: I Remember You
episodes.overview: The Ice King and Marceline bond over song and memories.

episodes.name: The Lich
episodes.overview: A visit from the Lich King sheds light on Ooo's secrets.

seasons.name: Season 5
seasons.overview: The season has been met with largely positive critical reception. In June 2013, the series was nominated for "Best Animated Series" at the 2013 Critics' Choice Television Awards. At the 65th Primetime Emmy Awards, "Simon & Marcy", was nominated for a Primetime Emmy Award for Short-format Animation, and former character designer Andy Ristaino won an Emmy for "Outstanding Individual Achievement In Animation" for his character designs in the episode "Puhoy".

episodes.name: Finn the Human
episodes.overview: Part 2 of a three-part episode. Finn and Jake chase the Lich through a dimensional portal and meet a wishmaster. After the Lich wishes that humanity never existed, Finn wishes that the Lich never existed.

episodes.name: Jake the Dog
episodes.overview: Part 3 of a three-part episode. Finn and Jake chase the Lich through a dimensional portal and meet a wishmaster. After the Lich wishes that humanity never existed, Finn wishes that the Lich never existed.

episodes.name: Five More Short Graybles
episodes.overview: A series of short stories all centered around a common theme, hosted by a mysterious man named Cuber from the future.

episodes.name: Up a Tree
episodes.overview: The guys' game of catch goes awry when their throwing disc is lodged in a large tree.

episodes.name: All the Little People
episodes.overview: Finn receives a bag full of miniature versions of his friends.

episodes.name: Jake the Dad
episodes.overview: Jake's a daddy, but being a father and keeping his rainicorn pups from killing themselves or each other is a lot harder than he imagined.

episodes.name: Davey
episodes.overview: Finn creates an alter ego, Davey. Davey soon begins to take over, and Jake is forced into action to get his old friend back.

episodes.name: Mystery Dungeon
episodes.overview: Ice King, NEPTR, Tree Trunks, Shelby, and Lemongrab are trapped inside a mysterious dungeon and must work together to free themselves.

episodes.name: All Your Fault
episodes.overview: Princess Bubblegum sends Finn and Jake to investigate a message of distress from the Earls of Lemongrab.

episodes.name: Little Dude
episodes.overview: Finn's hat comes to life and becomes evil after it is touched by a wizard. Finn, Jake, and the wizard track the hat down, and manage to turn the hat good.

episodes.name: Bad Little Boy
episodes.overview: The princesses tire of Ice King’s crazy Fionna-and-Cake fan-fiction stories, so Marceline stops by the Ice Kingdom to show him how to properly write a story.

episodes.name: Vault of Bones
episodes.overview: When Flame Princess begins to doubt her evilness, Finn insists she is not evil and takes her on a journey into a dungeon to help her sort out her thoughts.

episodes.name: The Great Bird Man
episodes.overview: Xergiok, the former Goblin king who was deposed by Finn and Jake claims to have turned over a new leaf.

episodes.name: Simon & Marcy
episodes.overview: A look at what Ice King and Marceline were like 996 years ago.

episodes.name: A Glitch Is a Glitch
episodes.overview: The Ice King creates a computer virus that will delete everyone in Ooo except for him and Princess Bubblegum. Finn and Jake hack into the universal source code to destroy the virus.

episodes.name: Puhoy
episodes.overview: Finn dreams he is in a pillow world where he marries a pillow woman  and has two children with her.

episodes.name: BMO Lost
episodes.overview: BMO makes his way home after being snatched by an eagle. On its way, BMO meets Bubble and a baby, and the three decide to journey home together.

episodes.name: Princess Potluck
episodes.overview: Ice King gets super jealous when he finds out that he wasn't invited to the Princess Potluck.

episodes.name: James Baxter the Horse
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake stumble across a horse named James Baxter who has the ability to make sad people feel better.

episodes.name: Shh!
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake make a bet to see who can not talk the longest, and the two use signs to communicate.

episodes.name: The Suitor
episodes.overview: Peppermint Butler thinks that Bubblegum is working too hard in her lab, so he tries to get her a suitor.

episodes.name: The Party's Over, Isla de Señorita
episodes.overview: After another one of his schemes fails, the Ice King decides to give up.

episodes.name: One Last Job
episodes.overview: Jake Jr. gets involved with a group of troublemakers, and Jake is forced to reunite his old gang—which includes Tiffany who first appeared in the first season episode "My Two Favorite People"—to rescue his daughter.

episodes.name: Another Five More Short Graybles
episodes.overview: A series of short stories with a common theme, hosted by a mysterious man named Cuber from the future. In this entry, Finn and Jake build a time machine. Meanwhile, Princess Bubblegum helps Cinnamon Bun overcome his fear of the dark.

episodes.name: Candy Streets
episodes.overview: Lumpy Space Princess is robbed, but before she is able to explain the details to Finn and Jake, she faints.

episodes.name: Wizards Only, Fools
episodes.overview: After Starchy comes down with a cold and needs a magic cure, Finn, Jake, and Princess Bubblegum disguise themselves as wizards and sneak into Wizard City.

episodes.name: Jake Suit
episodes.overview: Jake gets upset with the amount of times that Finn uses his body as a suit of armor, so he convinces Finn to trade places with him.

episodes.name: Be More
episodes.overview: BMO accidentally deletes his core system files. Finn and Jake disguise themselves as MOs to infiltrate the MO factory and save BMO from a memory wipe.

episodes.name: Sky Witch
episodes.overview: Marceline tracks the Sky Witch, but finds out that she may need Princess Bubblegum's help.

episodes.name: Frost & Fire
episodes.overview: Flame Princess and the Ice King fight each other, prompting Finn to have an interesting dream.

episodes.name: Too Old
episodes.overview: Finn, Jake and Princess Bubblegum discover a talented mutant named Lemonhope at The Pageant of Mutants. Now they must find a way to free him from the lemongrabs.

episodes.name: Earth & Water
episodes.overview: Princess Bubblegum subjects Flame Princess to a series of tests to gauge Flame Princess' fiery tendencies. But when there's an emergency at the treehouse, and Princess Bubblegum leaves Cinnamon Bun to watch Flame Princess, her experiment might literally backfire in her face.

episodes.name: Time Sandwich
episodes.overview: Jake crafts the most delicious sandwich ever, but when Magic Man steals it, Finn must defy the laws of space and time to win back Jake's creation.

episodes.name: The Vault
episodes.overview: When Finn starts sleepwalking and dreaming about the Green Lady he filed away in his memory vault, Jake and BMO help him tap into his repressed memories to uncover a secret past. Who is the Green Lady? And how is she connected to Finn?

episodes.name: Love Games
episodes.overview: Slime Princess needs a husband or else she'll lose the Slime Kingdom to her obnoxious sis. Finn steps in to save the day, but first they will need to win a series of Love Games to prove to Slime Princess's dad that they are really in love. This is definitely not what Finn signed up for!

episodes.name: Dungeon Train
episodes.overview: All aboard! Finn and Jake discover a train where every car is a dungeon filled with a new foe for Finn to fight. Jake quickly gets bored and wants to leave, but Finn is having the best time and doesn't want to leave... ever!

episodes.name: The Box Prince
episodes.overview: Finn meets the Box Prince—a cat with a box on its back—and learns that the Box Kingdom has been taken over by an imposter. Finn must therefore help the real Box Prince reclaim the throne.

episodes.name: Red Starved
episodes.overview: Finn, Jake and Marceline are trapped in an underground cavern with no red in sight. If Marceline doesn't feed, like ASAP, she will turn into a vampiric beast and suck out all of Jake's blood! So, Finn heads off to explore the cave and find something red to satiate her until they can be rescued. But time is running out!

episodes.name: We Fixed a Truck
episodes.overview: Finn finds an old truck, and Jake calls Banana Man to help with the repairs. But when BMO stays up all night working on the truck, he hears on a spooky radio talk show that Princess Bubblegum is a reptilian replicant. Is it just another one of Starchy's crazy conspiracy theories, or a fact?

episodes.name: Play Date
episodes.overview: Sick and tired of babysitting Ice King while the Ice Kingdom is being rebuilt, Finn and Jake call up an old friend to hang out with their annoying houseguest: Abracadaniel.

episodes.name: The Pit
episodes.overview: Finn needs Lady Rainicorn's help to rescue Jake when he is kidnapped by Kee-Oth the Blood Demon.

episodes.name: James
episodes.overview: Finn, Jake, and Princess Bubblegum are attacked by nasty goo monsters in the Desert of Wonders.

episodes.name: Root Beer Guy
episodes.overview: Root Beer Guy works a boring job during the day and tries to write mystery stories at night. But his life is about to change when he witnesses Finn and Jake kidnapping Princess Bubblegum! There's only one problem: no one believes Root Beer Guy...

episodes.name: Apple Wedding
episodes.overview: Tree Trunks and Mr. Pig are celebrating the wedding of the year.

episodes.name: Blade of Grass
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake decide it's time for Finn to get a new sword. Finn reluctantly buys a grass sword from a mysterious old man, but the sword turns out to be cursed! And unfortunately for our hero, all sales are final.

episodes.name: Rattleballs
episodes.overview: Finn practices his sword fighting skills at the candy junkyard, where he meets an old gumball robot named Rattleballs. To Finn's shock, he finds out he's not the master swordsman he thinks he is. What the what?! Finn begs Rattleballs to train him, but he soon discovers his mentor's deep, dark secret... a secret that will ultimately test Finn's loyalty to Princess Bubblegum.

episodes.name: The Red Throne
episodes.overview: When Flame King breaks out of his prison and takes over the Flame Kingdom again, Flame Princess turns to the one person she believes she can trust... Finn! But will Finn be able to put his feelings for Flame Princess aside long enough to help her reclaim her throne?

episodes.name: Betty
episodes.overview: After a magic spell backfires, the Ice King reverts back to Simon, and seeks help from Finn, Jake, and Marceline in order to get Betty, his former fiancée, back.

episodes.name: Bad Timing
episodes.overview: Love is in the air when Lumpy Space Princess reconnects with an old classmate, but will her jealousy get in the way of finding true love?

episodes.name: Lemonhope Part One
episodes.overview: Tired of all of Princess Bubblegum's talk about "responsibility," Lemonhope yearns for true freedom. So he sets off on the greatest adventure of his lemony life.

episodes.name: Lemonhope Part Two
episodes.overview: Though Lemonhope finds refuge from the desert with monster hunter Phlannel Boxingday, he might not be able to escape the ghosts of his past.

episodes.name: Billy's Bucket List
episodes.overview: Finn finds the hero Billy's bucket list and decides to complete the unfinished items as a final tribute.

seasons.name: Season 6
seasons.overview: The season follows the adventures of Finn the Human, a human boy, and his best friend Jake, a dog with magical powers to change shape, grow, and shrink at will. Finn and Jake live in the post-apocalyptic Land of Ooo. Along the way, they interact with the other main characters of the show: Princess Bubblegum, The Ice King, and Marceline the Vampire Queen. Common storylines revolve around Finn and Jake discovering strange creatures, dealing with the antagonistic but misunderstood Ice King, and battling monsters in order to help others.

episodes.name: Wake Up
episodes.overview: In order to find Finn's father, Finn and Jake must commit a cosmic crime...unless the Lich beats them to it.

episodes.name: Escape from the Citadel
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake follow the Lich to the Citadel, where Finn meets his long lost dad. But just how far does the apple fall from the tree?

episodes.name: James II
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake discover that Clone James has been faking his own death to collect medals. Now there are 25 Jameses running amok!

episodes.name: The Tower
episodes.overview: Finn doesn't like any of the new arms the princesses give him, so he builds a tower into space to find his dad and get his old arm back. But are his hopes up a little too high?

episodes.name: Sad Face
episodes.overview: Once a month, while Jake's asleep, his tail stretches out of the tree house to go work as a clown in a traveling bug circus.

episodes.name: Breezy
episodes.overview: With a friendly bee named "Breezy" as his wingman, Finn decides to get back into the dating game.

episodes.name: Food Chain
episodes.overview: On a field trip to the Candy Kingdom Museum of Natural History, Finn and Jake learn about the food chain by becoming the food chain!

episodes.name: Furniture & Meat
episodes.overview: Big money problems send Finn and Jake to Wildberry Kingdom.

episodes.name: The Prince Who Wanted Everything
episodes.overview: The beautiful and sensitive Lumpy Space Prince flees his cruel parents to start a new life.

episodes.name: Something Big
episodes.overview: Princess Bubblegum must rally her forces when the Candy Kingdom is rocked by a massive assault.

episodes.name: Little Brother
episodes.overview: Shelby the worm discovers that he has a little brother who is bound for adventure in the nooks of Marceline's tree house.

episodes.name: Ocarina
episodes.overview: Fed up with Jake's antics, his son Kim Kil Whan takes action.

episodes.name: Thanks for the Crabapples, Giuseppe
episodes.overview: Ice King and a band of misfit wizards go on a mystical road trip.

episodes.name: Princess Day
episodes.overview: It's Princess Day in Ooo! You know what that means? Yep, LSP and Marceline team up to prank Breakfast Princess!

episodes.name: Nemesis
episodes.overview: A shadowy figure named Peace Master targets the Candy Kingdom elite.

episodes.name: Joshua and Margaret Investigations
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake's parents hunt an unearthly menace in the woods.

episodes.name: Ghost Fly
episodes.overview: Jake and the tree house are haunted by a vengeful specter.

episodes.name: Everything's Jake
episodes.overview: Jake finds himself trapped in a world made of himself.

episodes.name: Is That You?
episodes.overview: Following an ally's memorial service, Jake begins acting strangely.

episodes.name: Jake the Brick
episodes.overview: Jake wants to fulfill a bizarre lifelong ambition.

episodes.name: Dentist
episodes.overview: When Finn's toothache gets too much to take, he has no choice but to go see dentist.

episodes.name: The Cooler
episodes.overview: When the Fire Kingdom is struck by a natural disaster, Flame Princess turns to an unlikely ally.

episodes.name: The Pajama War
episodes.overview: A Candy Kingdom slumber party devolves into panic when Finn and Princess Bubblegum vanish.

episodes.name: Evergreen
episodes.overview: In a distant age, the wizard Evergreen quests to save the world.

episodes.name: Astral Plane
episodes.overview: Finn's spirit is drawn into the astral plane by the power of the mysterious comet.

episodes.name: Gold Stars
episodes.overview: Tree Trunks and Mr. Pig's child, Sweet P, runs into trouble on his first day of school.

episodes.name: The Visitor
episodes.overview: Finn meets a friendly civilization and a sees a mysterious crash site in a vision.

episodes.name: The Mountain
episodes.overview: Lemongrab and Finn go on an expedition through the Mountain of Matthew.

episodes.name: Dark Purple
episodes.overview: Susan Strong and her allies infiltrate the mysterious Super Porp factory.

episodes.name: The Diary
episodes.overview: Jake's son TV discovers a lost diary and sets out to solve a decades-old mystery.

episodes.name: Walnuts & Rain
episodes.overview: When Finn and Jake stumble into two different holes, they meet two different fates.

episodes.name: Friends Forever
episodes.overview: Ice King has a plan to form a perfect circle of confidants.

episodes.name: Jermaine
episodes.overview: After a chilling dream encounter, Finn & Jake are determined to reconnect with their reclusive brother.

episodes.name: Chips And Ice Cream
episodes.overview: BMO's favorite entertainers unexpectedly find a new home at the tree house.

episodes.name: Graybles 1000+
episodes.overview: Marooned on an alien world, Cuber must rely on his bag of Graybles to survive.

episodes.name: Hoots
episodes.overview: A charismatic stranger in Finn's dream leads Cosmic Owl to shirk his duties.

episodes.name: Water Park Prank
episodes.overview: After rescuing Princess Orangutan from Daddy-sad-heads, Finn and Jake head to a post-apocalyptic water park for a day of fun.

episodes.name: You Forgot Your Floaties
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake storm Magic Man's house to rescue his new apprentice.

episodes.name: Be Sweet
episodes.overview: A fed up Lumpy Space Princess leaves the woods for a glamorous career in babysitting.

episodes.name: Orgalorg
episodes.overview: After a walrus race accident, Gunther starts to experience strange visions.

episodes.name: On the Lam
episodes.overview: Finn's dad Martin the Human fights for freedom on a strange new planet!

episodes.name: Hot Diggity Doom
episodes.overview: It's election day in the Candy Kingdom but Princess Bubblegum's attention is diverted by a mysterious presence in the sky.

episodes.name: The Comet
episodes.overview: Finn, Jake and Orgalorg converge with the comet and meet their destiny.

seasons.name: Season 7
seasons.overview: Main story arcs for this season include Bubblegum adjusting to life in exile and eventually reclaiming the Candy Kingdom crown, and Marceline coming to terms with her vampiric nature.

episodes.name: Bonnie & Neddy
episodes.overview: Under orders from the King of Ooo, Finn and Jake discover one of Ooo's greatest secrets.

episodes.name: Varmints
episodes.overview: Bubblegum turns to Marceline's help when something threatens the citizens of her homestead.

episodes.name: Cherry Cream Soda
episodes.overview: The arrival of a visitor causes Cherry Cream Soda's life to fall flat.

episodes.name: Mama Said
episodes.overview: The loyalty of Finn and Jake comes into question when the King of Ooo orders them to intercept a flying mushroom.

episodes.name: Football
episodes.overview: BMO and Football decide upon a deal, but one of them cannot keep up their end of the bargain.

episodes.name: Stakes Part 1: Marceline the Vampire Queen
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake hunt a shadowy predator and Marceline asks Princess Bubblegum for a favor.

episodes.name: Stakes Part 2: Everything Stays
episodes.overview: As the sun rises on her last day, Marceline recalls her long extraordinary life.

episodes.name: Stakes Part 3: Vamps About
episodes.overview: Five foes from Marceline's past come back to cause trouble for the Land of Ooo.

episodes.name: Stakes Part 4: Empress Eyes
episodes.overview: When one of her oldest adversaries targets the Ice Kingdom, Marceline rushes to Simon's rescue.

episodes.name: Stakes Part 5: May I Come In?
episodes.overview: Finn, Jake, Marceline, and PB set out to hunt down the Vamps. But who is hunting them?

episodes.name: Stakes Part 6: Take Her Back
episodes.overview: While Princess Bubblegum searches for a cure for Marceline, Finn and Jake take on one of the Vamps themselves.

episodes.name: Stakes Part 7: Checkmate
episodes.overview: On the eve of battle, Marceline's archenemy comes to her with a strange proposal.

episodes.name: Stakes Part 8: The Dark Cloud
episodes.overview: The final confrontation begins. Who will survive?

episodes.name: The More You Moe (1)
episodes.overview: It's BMO's birthday, and he gets to have his creator MO pay him a visit. Mo gives BMO a solo quest to go the factory and back.

episodes.name: The Moe You Know (2)
episodes.overview: BMO learns that all the others MO have been merged into 1 giant being, and of the brother he never knew he had.

episodes.name: Summer Showers
episodes.overview: Viola tries to get a part in LSP's play, but gets made into LSP's personal assistant instead.

episodes.name: Angel Face
episodes.overview: BMO convinces his friends to join him in a live action cowboy role-playing game.

episodes.name: President Porpoise Is Missing!
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake attempt to track down President Porpoise before Vice President Blowfish takes over.

episodes.name: Blank Eyed Girl
episodes.overview: One very spooky night, Finn and Jake come face-to-face with an urban myth.

episodes.name: Bad Jubies
episodes.overview: Finn, Jake, LSP and BMO seek shelter as they contend with some deadly weather.

episodes.name: King's Ransom
episodes.overview: Ice King suffers a heartbreaking loss and it's up to Finn and Jake to find the culprit.

episodes.name: Scamps
episodes.overview: Finn takes a group of at-risk Candy Kingdom youth on a camping trip they’ll never forget.

episodes.name: Crossover
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake crossover into Farmworld Finn's dimension.

episodes.name: The Hall of Egress
episodes.overview: Trapped and alone, Finn must unravel the riddle of the weird cave with no exit.

episodes.name: Flute Spell
episodes.overview: Finn has secret meetings with a powerful wizard.

episodes.name: The Thin Yellow Line
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake infiltrate the Banana Guard ranks and stumble upon a conspiracy.

episodes.name: Broke His Crown
episodes.overview: When Ice King's magic crown goes haywire, Marceline and Princess Bubblegum resort to extreme measures to help him.

episodes.name: Don't Look
episodes.overview: Finn unearths a treasure with a terrible price at the top of Dead Mountain.

episodes.name: Beyond the Grotto
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake follow their Sea Lard into the pond in front of their home, and in doing so, are led to a strange new world.

episodes.name: Lady Rainicorn of the Crystal Dimension
episodes.overview: Jake's son finds a hidden box and draws attention from a Rainicorn.

episodes.name: I am a Sword
episodes.overview: When Finn begins having nightmares about his missing Finn Sword, he wonders if they are real.

episodes.name: Bun Bun
episodes.overview: Finn brings a special delivery for Cinnamon Bun to the Fire Kingdom but it may come with a dangerous cost.

episodes.name: Normal Man
episodes.overview: Normal Man asks for Finn and Jake's help to rescue his brother.

episodes.name: Elemental
episodes.overview: Ice King digs up an item buried underneath the Ice Kingdom.

episodes.name: Five Short Tables
episodes.overview: Fionna and Cake go on a cooking adventure to push Cake's art to an all-new level.

episodes.name: The Music Hole
episodes.overview: Finn hears a mysterious song while judging a Battle of the Bands.

episodes.name: Daddy-Daughter Card Wars
episodes.overview: Jake and his daughter Charlie fight to restore Jake's honor and win a super-secret underground Card Wars tourney.

episodes.name: Two Swords
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake puzzle over the nature of a mysterious newcomer.

episodes.name: Do No Harm
episodes.overview: Doctor Princess thrusts a great responsibility upon Finn. Jake goes adventuring with a new friend.

episodes.name: Wheels
episodes.overview: Kim Kil Whan is worried about his daughter's future and asks Jake for some parental advice.

episodes.name: High Strangeness
episodes.overview: An otherworldly encounter puts Tree Trunks on the trail of a conspiracy in the Candy Kingdom.

episodes.name: Horse and Ball
episodes.overview: When disaster befalls James Baxter, it’s up to Finn and Jake to help him pick up the pieces.

episodes.name: Jelly Beans Have Power
episodes.overview: Princess Bubblegum's scientific mind must wrestle with her Elemental magic potential when she's faced with a Crystal Entity.

episodes.name: Islands Part 1: The Invitation
episodes.overview: A mysterious craft invades Ooo and Finn believes it may hold the secrets to his past.

episodes.name: Islands Part 2: Whipple the Happy Dragon
episodes.overview: Finn, Jake, and Susan set sail on a ocean voyage full of wonders and danger.

episodes.name: Islands Part 3: Mysterious Island
episodes.overview: After waking up alone and shipwrecked, Finn investigates a bizarre island in search of his friends.

episodes.name: Islands Part 4: Imaginary Resources
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake travel to a land where reality has been redesigned and improved.

episodes.name: Islands Part 5: Hide and Seek
episodes.overview: While exploring some futuristic ruins, Susan sees glimpses of a familiar girl.

episodes.name: Islands Part 6: Min & Marty
episodes.overview: An unexpected revelation from Susan leads Finn closer to answers about his past.

episodes.name: Islands Part 7: Helpers
episodes.overview: Finn and his friends journey to a last refuge called Founders Island.

episodes.name: Islands Part 8: The Light Cloud
episodes.overview: Finn confronts the power behind Founders Island, but will he ever return home to Ooo?

episodes.name: Orb
episodes.overview: While returning home from their adventure in Islands, Finn, Jake and BMO take a nap after eating a lot of bananas. A mysterious black orb in the sky begins to subject the three to strange dreams that quickly become nightmarish. Their nightmares begin to intertwine as they realize that they are dreaming and come in contact with a being that Finn dubs Nightmare Princess. This entity simply wants their bananas, but BMO strikes a bargain so that they get something in return. The group wake up to the orb taking some of their bananas and leaves a pink vile of nightmare juice. BMO looks through the telescope to discover that Ooo has changed radically.

episodes.name: Elements Part 1: Skyhooks
episodes.overview: Finn, Jake and BMO arrive back in Ooo and discover that their home and the areas surrounding it have been entirely converted into candy. They also encounter Fern, N.E.P.T.R., Shelby, Lemongrab, Tree Trunks, Mr. Pig and Marceline who have been converted into happily brainwashed candy people. A frightened Sweet P is the only person who is still normal and directs the gang to a mysterious candy tower. The tower turns out to be Princess Bubblegum who has become a large candy being and attempts to convert the gang into candy people as well. While BMO is completely transformed, Finn and Jake are rescued by Ice King who takes them to the Sky Kingdom. As Finn and Jake look down, they discover that Ooo has been divided into four completely corrupted sections.

episodes.name: Elements Part 2: Bespoken For
episodes.overview: Ice King explains what happened to Ooo while Finn and Jake were away. After the group left on their adventure, Ice King was visited by Betty (voiced by Felicia Day) who, frustrated over Ice King not remembering her, asks him out on a date. Betty recreates a restaurant from Ice King's previous life as Simon. When Ice King still can't remember his old life Betty drops him off back home and leaves him. Tiny Manticore gives Betty some advice; rather than trying to adhere to Simon, she should just reach out to him as Ice King due to her having changed as well. Betty returns to Ice King and they start playing together. Suddenly, Patience St. Pim (voiced by Lauren Lapkus) kidnaps Betty and begins using her magic to empower mind controlled Princess Bubblegum, Flame Princess and Slime Princess while Ice King flees with Gunter.

episodes.name: Elements Part 3: Winter Light
episodes.overview: Finn, Jake and Ice King travel to the Ice World and break through the large ice dome covering the center of the land. They encounter Carroll (voiced by Cameron Esposito), from "The Tower", who was converted to Ice and is genuinely pleased with her new appearance. The gang eventually encounter a powered up, and rather withheld, Patience who seems disappointed with the outcome of the new Ooo. While she succeeded in empowering the other elementals they have relegated themseleves to their sections of Ooo as Patience had forced them to power up rather than allow them to do so themseleves. The gang rescue Betty and leave while Patience bemoans the new world to an iced Choose Goose. Betty reveals that she can help them with the power of the Enchiridion which Finn has, causing Betty to ominously laugh.

episodes.name: Elements Part 4: Cloudy
episodes.overview: In order to calm Finn down, Jake tucks him and himself into a cloud, but it floats away from Ice King and Betty. The two find themselves floating in the middle of endless sky while another cloud with a door flies past them. The two play pretend barber to pass the time and end up getting to the roots of their worries. The cloud flies past again and discover that it is actually a lard. They use the lard to fly back to Betty and Ice King where the former has discovered a way to return the land of Ooo to normal.

episodes.name: Elements Part 5: Slime Central
episodes.overview: Finn and Jake arrive in the transformed Slime Kingdom to retrieve Slime Princess' crown for her jewel. They run into Lumpy Space Princess who is attending Slime Princess's roller skating party. The winners of the skating competition get absorbed into Slime Princess's whole being while the losers are caged up. Finn, Jake and Lumpy Space Princess enter, but lose, only to learn that by losing they still get absorbed. While Finn manages to grab the crown, Jake gets fully absorbed into Slime Princess forcing Lumpy Space Princess to save Finn, revealing in the process that 'her lumps' protect her from corruption. They are ejected from Slime Princess and forced to leave. Finn is saddened at the loss of Jake, but Lumpy Space Princess explains that Finn and Jake always win which inspires Finn to continue his mission.

episodes.name: Elements Part 6: Happy Warrior
episodes.overview: Finn, Lumpy Space Princess, and Gunter arrive in a radically altered Fire Kingdom. The inhabitants, which include Wyatt (voiced by Andrew Daly) and Lady Rainicorn, attack the heroes. Finn and Gunter try desperately to restrain their violent tendencies as it would allow the kingdom to corrupt them. Eventually the group find Flame Princess who has transformed into a dragon. When she swallows the jewel necessary to save Ooo, Finn gives into his violence and begins attacking Flame Princess. Lumpy Space Princess angered by the violence yells at everyone to stop their fighting. The kingdom misinterprets her anger and decide to start a war with the Candy Kingdom. Cinnamon Bun, who was unaffected by the corruption, frets that this is the end of Ooo.

episodes.name: Elements Part 7: Hero Heart
episodes.overview: Lumpy Space Princess chases Finn and attempts to turn him back to normal, but to no avail. Ice King and Betty try to intervene, but are swatted away by Flame Princess. The Fire Kingdom inhabitants 'fight' the Candy Kingdom inhabitants making Lumpy Space Princess upset. After eating some of Marceline, who is made of marshmallows, Lumpy Space Princess reaches out to Finn's hero heart by placing some of Princess Bubblegum onto him. Recalling happier times with PB, Finn returns to normal. PB then fires her candy powers into the air and converts everyone into obedient candy people, except for Finn who was protected by Lumpy Space Princess. Finn nabs the three jewels and gives them to Betty, but she leaves him behind. Finn finds himself surrounded by the Candy Kingdom.

episodes.name: Elements Part 8: Skyhooks II
episodes.overview: Betty knocks out Ice King and reveals that she wants to use the jewels to go back in time and stop Simon from transforming into Ice King. Ice King, still oblivious to her plans accidentally ruins her spell causing her to get transported to Mars where she meets Normal Man. Lumpy Space Princess rescues Finn from the candy inhabitants as Princess Bubblegum enacts her plan to convert the rest of Ooo into candy while Patience freezes herself again. Finn realizes that LSP's immunity means that she is the anti-elemental. Ice King arrives with the gems and Lumpy Space Princess is able to transform all of Ooo back to normal. However, Jake comes back resembling his shapeshifter parent. Despite this, Finn is glad that he is reunited with his brother.

episodes.name: Abstract
episodes.overview: Finn, BMO and Lady Rainicorn are slightly disturbed by Jake's new alien appearance while Jake himself seems oblivious, or rather in denial about it. After having a bizarre dream about Jermaine (voiced by Tom Scharpling) painting abstract art, which according to Jake he hates, he decides to go look for him. Jake traverses the wasteland until he comes across Jermaine's studio. He tries to "rescue" Jermaine from changing, but Jermaine convinces Jake that change is a good thing as long as you remain the same on the inside. After examining and taking home one of Jermaine's paintings, Jake discovers that he has returned to normal and is greeted by a very pleased Finn.

episodes.name: Ketchup
episodes.overview: Marceline is unexpectedly visited by BMO causing the former to ask BMO to download a USB drive. While they wait, BMO tells the story of when it, Finn and Jake traveled the seas. However, the story is mostly inaccurate and involves a cat named Ted and a blue jay that says "OOOOOOHH!" (voiced by J. G. Quintel). Marcy then tells the story of "Lollipop Girl" and "Rock Star Girl" and their encounter with a "Blue Tranch" that resulted in "Weekend Island" getting taken over by potatoes. When the USB drive finally downloads, it reveals pictures of young Marcy with her mother. She feigns knowing them and asks BMO to tell their story resulting in a tale about "the Child and the Moon Girl" which Marcy thanks BMO for.

episodes.name: Fionna and Cake and Fionna
episodes.overview: At a Fionna and Cake book reading by Ice King, an old woman claiming to be Fionna (voiced by Charlotte Newhouse) arrives with a tape of an early Fionna and Cake adventure. Ice King is enamored by "Fionna" and invites her to stay with him. At night Ice King watches the remainder of the tape where Fionna and Cake find a mummy (voiced by Chelsea Peretti) only to learn that the mummy is really the Queen of Ooo. Ice King misinterprets the video and thinks that "Fionna" is a mummy. He confronts her and discovers that she was looking for more Fionna and Cake tapes only to find that Ice King doesn't have any. "Fionna" is really a bunny who picked up signals that played Fionna and Cake and wanted more. When she realizes what she has done she flees. Later that night, Fionna and Cake adventures are beamed into Ice King's head.

episodes.name: Whispers
episodes.overview: While fishing, Finn and Fern encounter Sweet P who was running away from home after having a nightmare. Sweet P reveals that he has been having visions of a "whisper monster" trying to tell him he is evil. Finn and Fern decide to camp with Sweet P when they encounter the hand of the Lich that was cut off in "Crossover". Finn and Fern fight the Lich's hand, but it escapes. Finn gives chase and follows it into an underground tunnel where he ends up getting rescued by Sweet P (he had knocked out Fern so he could escape) who slays the hand. Fern feeling useless for not being able to help, plots to become the true Finn.

episodes.name: Three Buckets
episodes.overview: Fern reveals his ability to change his appearance to look just like Finn. Impressed, Finn joins Fern to a dungeon hidden away in a mountain. While there, Fern traps Finn in one of the rooms and reveals his plan to replace him. Finn finds out that his robotic arm can do a variety of things and drills his way out of the dungeon. Finn and Fern fight out in the field where Finn attempts to reason with Fern, however his robot arm misinterprets the word "finality" with "fatality" and he ends up destroying Fern. Finn returns home traumatized with Jake and BMO comforting him. Meanwhile, a mysterious man (voiced by Fred Melamed) scoops up Fern's still living remains in a bucket.

seasons.name: Season 10
seasons.overview: The tenth and final season of Adventure Time.

episodes.name: The Wild Hunt
episodes.overview: A fierce creature is terrorizing the Candy Kingdom but before Finn can slay the beast, he must first overcome a guilty conscience.

episodes.name: Always BMO Closing
episodes.overview: BMO and Ice King hit the road as door to door salesmen and stumble upon an irresistible opportunity.

episodes.name: Son of Rap Bear
episodes.overview: When Flame Princess is coaxed into a high stakes battle against the indomitable Son of Rap Bear, Finn must help her search for a new strategy.

episodes.name: Bonnibel Bubblegum
episodes.overview: A long lost artifact causes Princess Bubblegum to harken back to the creation of the Candy Kingdom.

episodes.name: Seventeen
episodes.overview: A mysterious knight crashes Finn's birthday bash and presents him with a dangerous gift.

episodes.name: Ring of Fire
episodes.overview: When an old flame comes calling on urgent business, Tree Trunks reconsiders both her wild past and her tranquil present.

episodes.name: Marcy & Hunson
episodes.overview: Finn is needing a new sword, so he enlists the help of Peppermint Butler, who forges a weapon, the Night Blade, and then summons Hunson Abadeer (voiced by Martin Olson) to infuse it with "Nightosphere magic". Released unto Ooo, Abadeer initially tries to harvest souls, but Peppermint Butler binds him with a spell, rendering his powerless. Abadeer then decides to accompany Finn and Jake to the house of his daughter, Marceline the Vampire Queen (voiced by Olivia Olson).

episodes.name: The First Investigation
episodes.overview: Kim Kil Whan tasks Jake and Finn to investigate reports of a haunting in one of Kim Kil Whan's properties "Joshua and Margaret Investigations" since something in there traumatized his top employee Renny Hamlond and does not pay any rent for inhabiting the place.

episodes.name: Blenanas
episodes.overview: Finn's latest literary work meets with only derision, so he sets out to prove all the naysayers wrong.

episodes.name: Jake the Starchild
episodes.overview: In order to fulfill his grand destiny, Jake is spirited away by a strangely familiar shape-shifting alien.

episodes.name: Temple of Mars
